<body><h1 id="sunpor-ai-production-system-architecture">SUNPOR AI Production System - Architecture</h1>
<p><strong>Version:</strong> v2 (end-to-end)  |  <strong>Scope:</strong> Extrusion Line E10  |  <strong>Based on:</strong> 104 machine signals + the full operator input-form set.</p>
<hr />
<h2 id="table-of-contents">Table of contents</h2>
<ol>
<li>Context &amp; objectives</li>
<li>Guiding principles</li>
<li>System overview</li>
<li>Data model (PostgreSQL)</li>
<li>Time-series storage, scaling &amp; retention</li>
<li>Signals &amp; feature engineering</li>
<li>Data ingestion &amp; integration</li>
<li>Operator UI forms</li>
<li>Frontend architecture</li>
<li>Backend API</li>
<li>ML strategy (6 models)</li>
<li>MLOps: training, labels, registry, retraining</li>
<li>Alerting &amp; warnings</li>
<li>Authentication, authorization &amp; roles</li>
<li>Observability, logging &amp; monitoring</li>
<li>Security &amp; data governance</li>
<li>Deployment &amp; infrastructure</li>
<li>Testing &amp; QA</li>
<li>Reuse vs build new vs drop (ZITTA -&gt; SUNPOR)</li>
<li>Team responsibilities</li>
<li>Delivery plan (priority order)</li>
<li>Acceptance criteria</li>
<li>Open items / decisions needed</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2 id="1-context-objectives">1. Context &amp; objectives</h2>
<p>We are <strong>not building a new app</strong>. We clone the existing ZITTA system (<code>live_monitor/</code>) onto a fresh SUNPOR sandbox, give it an <strong>empty PostgreSQL database</strong>, remove all ZITTA-specific hardcoding, and re-fit it to SUNPOR's real machine (Extrusion Line <strong>E10</strong>). The system grows from "detect machine state + sensor anomalies" into a <strong>long-term production-intelligence platform</strong> that predicts <strong>quality problems and maintenance needs before they cause scrap</strong>.</p>
<p>The key new ingredient versus ZITTA is <strong>operator input forms that produce ML labels</strong>, which turns the machine learning from unsupervised into supervised.</p>
<p><strong>The four questions the system must answer (req. §1):</strong>
1. Which production phase is the line currently in? (9 phases)
2. Are quality problems developing early? (lumps, twin beads, pentane, foaming, etc.)
3. What are the relationships between production, material, maintenance, and quality?
4. Can it warn before scrap or quality defects occur?</p>
<hr />
<h2 id="2-guiding-principles">2. Guiding principles</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Nothing hardcoded</strong> (req. §12, §13). All signals, dropdowns, events, quality reasons, and prediction targets live in the DB and are editable. ZITTA's hardcoded <code>Val_1</code>, <code>REGIME_LOW_MAX</code>, fixed state lists are removed/abstracted.</li>
<li><strong>Configurable + historically safe.</strong> Dropdown values can be <strong>deactivated, never deleted</strong> - old records keep referencing old values.</li>
<li><strong>Multi-tenant from day one</strong> (req. §4.1). Every row is scoped by <code>company</code> -&gt; <code>production_line</code> -&gt; <code>machine_area</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Build in priority order</strong> (req. §11). Plumbing and data capture first; ML later, because ML needs labels that only exist once operators enter data.</li>
<li><strong>Simple ML first</strong> (req. §7, §8). Rule-based + Random Forest / XGBoost / LightGBM and Isolation Forest before any deep/temporal model.</li>
<li><strong>Factor scaling is mandatory</strong> (req. §4.5). Each signal has a <code>factor</code>; raw <code>2300 x 0.1 = 230.0</code>. Store both raw and scaled.</li>
<li><strong>Reuse ZITTA where proven</strong>, replace only what is single-machine or hardcoded.</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2 id="3-system-overview">3. System overview</h2>
<pre><code>   WinCC / OPC (Line E10, 104 tags)
            |
            v
  +-------------------------------------------------------------+
  |                  SUNPOR Sandbox Server                       |
  |                                                             |
  |  [Ingestion Service]  --factor scaling--&gt;  signal_timeseries |
  |        |                                                    |
  |        v                                                    |
  |  [Feature Engine] (config-driven, multi-window)             |
  |        |                                                    |
  |        v                                                    |
  |  [ML Service] (6 models) &lt;---- labels (operator forms)      |
  |        |                                                    |
  |        v                                                    |
  |  ml_prediction  --&gt;  [Alerting]                             |
  |        |                                                    |
  |        v                                                    |
  |  [Backend API - FastAPI]                                    |
  |        ^                                                    |
  |  [Scheduler/Jobs]   [Auth]   [Logging/Monitoring]           |
  +--------|----------------------------------------------------+
           | REST / JSON
           v
  [Frontend - React + TypeScript]
   8 operator forms + dashboards + admin/config + alerts
</code></pre>
