<h2 id="4-data-model-postgresql-req-4">4. Data model (PostgreSQL) - req. §4</h2>
<p>15 tables: the 11 from the requirements, plus four supporting tables (2 config, 1 baseline, 1 user/audit) that implement "nothing hardcoded", thresholds, and auth/audit.</p>
<h3 id="41-entity-relationships">4.1 Entity relationships</h3>
<pre><code>company (1) --&lt; production_line (1) --&lt; machine_area (1) --&lt; signal_catalog (1) --&lt; signal_timeseries
                     |
                     +--&lt; production_run (1) --&lt; production_event
                                             --&lt; material_behavior_event
                                             --&lt; material_block
                                             --&lt; daily_quality_input
                                             --&lt; ml_prediction
signal_catalog (1) --&lt; feature_baseline   (per signal + state thresholds)
app_user (1) --&lt; audit_log
</code></pre>
<h3 id="42-core-tables-req-4">4.2 Core tables (req. §4)</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Table</th>
<th>Purpose / key fields</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>company</code></td>
<td>Tenant root. <code>id, name, location, description, created_at, updated_at</code>. e.g. SUNPOR / Extrusion / Line E10.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>production_line</code></td>
<td><code>id, company_id, name, description, machine_area, active</code>. e.g. Extrusion E10.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>machine_area</code></td>
<td><code>id, production_line_id, name, type</code>. Extruder, Heating Zones, Granulator, Water Box, Screen Changer, Feeders, Off-spec.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>signal_catalog</code></td>
<td>Core. One row per WinCC tag. <code>id, company_id, production_line_id, machine_area_id, wincc_tag, display_name, unit, datatype, factor, signal_group, signal_role, active, description</code>. Seeded from <code>signal_catalog_seed.csv</code> (104 rows).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>signal_timeseries</code></td>
<td>Live + historical values. <code>timestamp, signal_id, value_raw, value_scaled, quality, source, imported_at</code>. <code>value_scaled = value_raw x factor</code>. (See §5 for scaling/partitioning.)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>production_run</code></td>
<td>Container. <code>id, company_id, production_line_id, start_time, end_time, material_type, is_trial, shift, operator, status, comment</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>production_event</code></td>
<td>Operator events (3-level). <code>id, production_run_id, event_time, level_1, level_2, level_3, reason, comment, operator, created_at</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>material_behavior_event</code></td>
<td>Early quality observations. <code>id, production_run_id, event_time, behavior_type, severity, comment, operator</code>. -&gt; ML labels (Model 3).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>material_block</code></td>
<td>Retroactive "this run was bad". <code>id, production_run_id, reason, from_time, to_time, affected_material, comment, created_by</code>. -&gt; ML label (Model 4).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>daily_quality_input</code></td>
<td>Daily/per-shift targets. <code>id, production_run_id, shift, input_time, open_holes_percent, sieve_distribution_percent, foaming_behavior, comment</code>. -&gt; ML targets (Model 4).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>ml_prediction</code></td>
<td>All model outputs. <code>id, timestamp, production_run_id, model_name, model_version, prediction_type, prediction_value, confidence, input_window_start, input_window_end, explanation, created_at</code>.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3 id="43-supporting-tables-new">4.3 Supporting tables (new)</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Table</th>
<th>Purpose / key fields</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>config_dropdown</code></td>
<td>Generic configurable dropdown store. <code>id, form_key, field_key, level_1, level_2, level_3, value_en, value_de, requires_reason, requires_text, sort_order, active</code>. Seeded from <code>input_form_taxonomy_seed.json</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>config_prediction_target</code></td>
<td>Configurable ML prediction types/labels so new targets are added without code changes (req. §12).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>feature_baseline</code></td>
<td>Per-signal + per-state baseline stats and thresholds (replaces ZITTA's 3 hardcoded regimes). <code>id, signal_id, state, feature_name, mean, std, p10, p90, warn_low, warn_high, crit_low, crit_high, sample_count, confidence, updated_at</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>app_user</code> / <code>audit_log</code></td>
<td>Auth + change history. <code>app_user(id, username, role, active, ...)</code>; <code>audit_log(id, user_id, entity, entity_id, action, before, after, created_at)</code>.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Prediction types</strong> (req. §4.11): <code>process_state, low_production, quality_risk, material_behavior_risk, granulator_risk, pressure_problem_risk, maintenance_risk</code>.</p>
<h3 id="44-migration-note-zitta-sunpor">4.4 Migration note (ZITTA -&gt; SUNPOR)</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>machine_sensor_raw</code> -&gt; <code>signal_timeseries</code> (generalized, catalog-driven).</li>
<li><code>live_process_window</code> / <code>window_features</code> -&gt; feature windows keyed by <code>signal_id</code>.</li>
<li><code>live_run_evaluation</code> -&gt; <code>ml_prediction</code>.</li>
<li><code>baseline_registry</code> -&gt; <code>feature_baseline</code> (per signal + state, not 3 fixed regimes).</li>
<li>Migrations managed with <strong>Alembic</strong>; seed scripts load <code>signal_catalog</code> and <code>config_dropdown</code> from the English seed files.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="5-time-series-storage-scaling-retention">5. Time-series storage, scaling &amp; retention</h2>
<p>The highest-volume part of the system. With 104 signals polled continuously, row counts grow fast (e.g. at 1 Hz that is ~9M rows/day; even at 10 s it is ~900k/day).</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Storage engine:</strong> plain PostgreSQL with <strong>native range partitioning by month</strong> on <code>signal_timeseries</code>, OR <strong>TimescaleDB</strong> hypertables (recommended if available - automatic chunking, compression, continuous aggregates). Decision is an open item (§23).</li>
<li><strong>Indexing:</strong> composite index on <code>(signal_id, timestamp)</code>; BRIN index on <code>timestamp</code> for large scans.</li>
<li><strong>Write path:</strong> batched/<code>COPY</code> inserts from the ingestion service, not row-by-row.</li>
<li><strong>Scaling on write:</strong> persist both <code>value_raw</code> and <code>value_scaled</code> so analytics never re-derive the factor.</li>
<li><strong>Retention &amp; downsampling:</strong> keep raw at full resolution for a configurable window (e.g. 90-180 days), then downsample to 1-min/5-min rollups for long-term history (continuous aggregates if TimescaleDB). Retention is configurable, not hardcoded.</li>
<li><strong>Pre-computed feature windows:</strong> store rolling-window features in a separate <code>feature_window</code> table so ML/training/dashboards don't recompute from raw each time.</li>
<li><strong>Data quality:</strong> <code>quality</code> column flags missing/stale/out-of-range readings so feature engineering and training can exclude them.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="6-signals-feature-engineering-req-6-9">6. Signals &amp; feature engineering - req. §6, §9</h2>
<p><code>SignalExport.xlsx</code> contains <strong>104 signals</strong> for Line E10. Full English catalog: <code>signal_catalog_seed.csv</code>.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>signal_group</th>
<th style="text-align: right;">Count</th>
<th>Machine area(s)</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>heating_zones</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">27</td>
<td>Heating Zones</td>
<td>9 zones x {setpoint, actual, control_output}. Zones 1-7 = Cylinder, 8 = Flange, 9 = Material Discharge Section.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>feeders</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">31</td>
<td>Feeders</td>
<td>Total throughput + Feeders 1-7 (EPS, Graphite, Recycled, 600, Off-spec, Pentane, Nitrogen): throughput, speed, error bitfields, operating modes.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>screen_changer</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">12</td>
<td>Screen Changer / Startup Valve / Die Plate</td>
<td>Inlet/outlet pressure, die plates 1-4, adapter, zones. factor 0.1.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>process_water</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">8</td>
<td>Water Box</td>
<td>Pressure P1/P2, temperature act/set, flow act/set, pump speed.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>granulator</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">6</td>
<td>Granulator</td>
<td>Speed act/set, torque, knife position, contact force act/set.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>melt_pressure</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">5</td>
<td>Extruder</td>
<td>Melt pressure 1-4, melt temperature 1.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>offspec</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">5</td>
<td>Off-spec</td>
<td>Scrap line, octabin, silo, sieve coarse, sieve fine.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>pentane_nitrogen</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">5</td>
<td>Pentane / Nitrogen / Antistatic</td>
<td>Pentane qty, nitrogen qty, pentane pump freq, antistatic act/set.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>extruder_meltpump</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">4</td>
<td>Extruder / Melt Pump</td>
<td>Screw speed, torque, melt pump speed, melt pump torque.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>status</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">1</td>
<td>-</td>
<td>Material Production flag (1 = producing).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Total</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">104</td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Key facts from the real file:</strong>
- <strong>Factor varies</strong>: heating/extruder signals = <code>1</code>; screen-changer/water/granulator (<code>E10G...</code> tags) = <code>0.1</code>.
- <strong>Datatypes</strong>: <code>WORD</code>, <code>REAL</code>, <code>BYTE</code>. Feeder errors are WORD bitfields (14 bits); operating modes are BYTE enums - decoded via reference codes in the taxonomy seed.
- <strong>Units</strong>: C, %, BAR, UPM (RPM), kg/h, m3/h, mm, Hz, kg, l/h.</p>
<p><strong>Standard feature set</strong> per signal, per window: <code>mean, min, max, std, last, first, slope, delta, range, instability_score</code>. <strong>Group-specific features:</strong>
- Temperature: setpoint/actual deviation per zone, max/avg deviation, control-output load, zone 1-&gt;9 gradient/profile.
- Pressure: trend, fluctuation, melt-pressure 1-4 differences, screen-changer inlet/outlet difference, pressure-to-throughput ratio.
- Throughput/Feeders: actual/setpoint deviation (total + per feeder), material shares, recycled share, off-spec share, EPS/graphite ratio, feeder error bits, operating-mode changes, low-production index.
- Granulator: torque trend, speed deviation, contact-force deviation, knife-position change, torque/speed ratio.
- Pentane/Nitrogen: pentane per kg throughput, pentane deviation, nitrogen trend, pentane-to-material-type ratio.
- Off-spec: off-spec per hour / per run, coarse/fine ratio, scrap rate, increase trend.</p>
<p><strong>Time windows</strong> (req. §8): <code>1, 5, 15, 30 min</code>, full-run window, and the critical <strong>"N minutes before an event"</strong> window (e.g. 30 min before a knife change or material block) - what enables <em>prediction</em> rather than detection.</p>
<hr />
<h2 id="7-data-ingestion-integration">7. Data ingestion &amp; integration</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Source:</strong> WinCC / OPC for Line E10 (exact host/protocol/poll-rate is an open item, §23). Until available, develop against historical exports (ZITTA used an HTTP poll in <code>config.API_URL</code>).</li>
<li><strong>Modes:</strong> (a) <strong>live polling</strong> at a configurable interval; (b) <strong>historical backfill</strong> from exports for training; both write to <code>signal_timeseries</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Pipeline:</strong> fetch raw values -&gt; map tag to <code>signal_catalog</code> -&gt; apply <code>factor</code> -&gt; write <code>value_raw</code> + <code>value_scaled</code> + <code>quality</code> + <code>source</code> -&gt; batch insert.</li>
<li><strong>Robustness:</strong> retry/backoff on source failure, never crash the loop (reuse ZITTA pattern); log and skip bad cycles.</li>
<li><strong>Data quality handling:</strong> detect missing/stale tags, out-of-range values, timestamp gaps; record in <code>quality</code>; produce a data-quality report (req. §10 Data Engineer deliverable).</li>
<li><strong>Timezones:</strong> store UTC; convert in the UI.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
