<p><strong>Material types</strong>: 750, 750GEN2, 750PremGEN2, 753, 753PremGEN2 + Trial flag.</p>
<hr />
<h2 id="9-frontend-architecture">9. Frontend architecture</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Stack:</strong> React + TypeScript SPA; build with Vite; component library for fast forms (e.g. Material UI or Ant Design).</li>
<li><strong>State/data:</strong> React Query (server cache) + typed API client generated from the FastAPI OpenAPI schema.</li>
<li><strong>Dynamic forms:</strong> form fields and 3-level cascading dropdowns are rendered from <code>GET /config/forms/{form_key}</code> - no dropdown values hardcoded in the frontend (req. §5).</li>
<li><strong>Screens:</strong></li>
<li>Operator: the 8 entry forms, optimized for fast shop-floor input (large controls, minimal typing, current production-run context auto-attached).</li>
<li>Dashboard: current process state, low-production status, live signal tiles, anomaly/quality-risk indicators, recent predictions.</li>
<li>Alerts: active warnings list + acknowledgement.</li>
<li>Admin/config: manage dropdowns, signals, prediction targets, users (deactivate-not-delete).</li>
<li><strong>UX safeguards:</strong> validation, confirmation on submit, offline-tolerant queueing for shop-floor reliability.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="10-backend-api-fastapi">10. Backend API (FastAPI)</h2>
<p>Endpoint families (consumed by the React frontend). All list endpoints paginated; standard error envelope; request/response validated with Pydantic.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Config / dropdowns</strong> - <code>GET /config/forms/{form_key}</code>, <code>GET /config/dropdowns</code>, admin <code>POST/PATCH</code> (deactivate, never delete).</li>
<li><strong>Production runs</strong> - <code>POST /production-runs</code>, <code>PATCH /production-runs/{id}</code> (end run), <code>GET /production-runs</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Events</strong> - <code>POST /events</code>, <code>POST /material-behavior</code>, <code>POST /material-blocks</code>, <code>POST /daily-quality</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Signals</strong> - <code>GET /signals</code> (catalog), <code>GET /signals/{id}/timeseries</code> (time-range, downsampled).</li>
<li><strong>ML / predictions</strong> - <code>GET /predictions/current</code>, <code>GET /predictions/history</code>, <code>GET /ml/model-status</code>, <code>POST /ml/trigger-retrain</code> (reuse from ZITTA).</li>
<li><strong>Alerts</strong> - <code>GET /alerts</code>, <code>POST /alerts/{id}/ack</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Auth</strong> - <code>POST /auth/login</code>, <code>GET /auth/me</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Health</strong> - <code>GET /health</code> (services, ML models loaded, scheduler status - reuse ZITTA pattern).</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="11-ml-strategy-6-models-req-7-8">11. ML strategy (6 models) - req. §7, §8</h2>
<p>Built in order; each later model depends on earlier ones knowing the process state.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>#</th>
<th>Model</th>
<th>Type (initial)</th>
<th>Inputs</th>
<th>Output / Labels</th>
<th>Prereq</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>Process State Classification (9 phases)</td>
<td>Rule-based + RandomForest/XGBoost</td>
<td>throughput, extruder speed/torque, melt pressure/temp, heating zones, melt pump, feeder modes, operator events</td>
<td>state + confidence + phase start/end</td>
<td>Built first</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2</td>
<td>Low Production Detection</td>
<td>RF/XGBoost + rules</td>
<td>throughput act/set, feeders, extruder speed/torque, melt pressure, operator events, modes</td>
<td>low-prod yes/no + duration + intensity + cause</td>
<td>Needs Model 1</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>Material Behavior Risk</td>
<td>LightGBM/XGBoost (supervised)</td>
<td>temp/pressure profile, throughput, feeder shares, pentane/nitrogen, water, granulator, material type, phase</td>
<td>risk per behavior (lumps, twin beads, sieve, pentane, foaming)</td>
<td>Needs labels from Form 8.6</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>4</td>
<td>Predictive Quality</td>
<td>LightGBM/XGBoost</td>
<td>full stable-phase data, material type, events, maintenance, behavior, off-spec, daily quality</td>
<td>open-holes / sieve / foaming / blocking risk</td>
<td>Needs labels from Forms 8.7, 8.8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>5</td>
<td>Granulator / Knife</td>
<td>RF/XGBoost</td>
<td>granulator speed/torque, knife position, contact force, water, off-spec, sieve, maintenance events</td>
<td>knife condition + grain-distribution risk + maintenance recommendation</td>
<td>Needs labels from Form 8.3</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>6</td>
<td>Nozzle / Screen Changer / Pressure</td>
<td>RF/XGBoost + rules</td>
<td>melt pressure 1-4, screen-changer in/out pressure, startup valve, die plate temps, melt temp, extruder/melt-pump torque</td>
<td>pressure problem + likely cause</td>
<td>Needs labels from Forms 8.2, 8.5</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Anomalies</strong> (cross-cutting): Isolation Forest / robust Z-score / PCA (reuse ZITTA per-state Isolation Forest). Autoencoder/temporal models only later.</p>
<p><strong>Phase classes</strong> (Model 1): Heating Up, Startup, Stable Production, Low Production, Cleaning Run, Empty Run, Cooling Down, Shutdown, Fault.</p>
<hr />
<h2 id="12-mlops-training-labels-registry-retraining">12. MLOps: training, labels, registry, retraining</h2>
<p>This is how raw data + operator labels become trained models.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Label join (the core idea):</strong> operator events (<code>production_event</code>, <code>material_behavior_event</code>, <code>material_block</code>, <code>daily_quality_input</code>) are time-joined to feature windows to build supervised training sets. Example: a material block from 14:00-15:00 labels all stable-production windows in that range as "bad"; a knife change at 09:00 labels the 30-min pre-event window for Model 5.</li>
<li><strong>Training-set assembly:</strong> a job builds <code>(features, label)</code> datasets per model from <code>feature_window</code> + labels, excluding cleaning/empty/low-production periods where required (req. §5.4, §7.2).</li>
<li><strong>Model registry:</strong> version every model (<code>model_name</code>, <code>model_version</code>), store artifacts + metrics; <code>ml_prediction</code> records which version produced each output (reuse ZITTA <code>ml/model_registry.py</code>).</li>
<li><strong>Evaluation:</strong> track accuracy/precision/recall per model; minimum-sample gates before a model goes live (reuse ZITTA <code>ANOMALY_MIN_SAMPLES_*</code> pattern, generalized).</li>
<li><strong>Retraining:</strong> scheduled (e.g. daily if enough new labeled rows) + manual trigger via API (reuse <code>ml/retrain_scheduler.py</code>). New models are promoted only if they pass evaluation gates.</li>
<li><strong>Drift detection:</strong> monitor feature drift vs baseline; raise alerts (reuse <code>ml/drift_detector.py</code>).</li>
<li><strong>Explainability:</strong> populate <code>ml_prediction.explanation</code> with the top contributing features/rules (rule text now; SHAP later).</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="13-alerting-warnings-req-1-point-4">13. Alerting &amp; warnings - req. §1 (point 4)</h2>
<p>The "warn before scrap" requirement.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Sources:</strong> anomaly score, quality-risk predictions (Models 3-6), drift detection, feeder errors, data-quality failures.</li>
<li><strong>Rule engine:</strong> configurable thresholds (stored in DB, not hardcoded) decide when a prediction/score becomes a warning (info / warning / critical).</li>
<li><strong>Delivery:</strong> in-app alert center first; optional email/Teams/webhook later. Each alert has <code>state, severity, message, source, created_at, acknowledged_by</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Lifecycle:</strong> raise -&gt; acknowledge -&gt; auto-resolve when condition clears.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="14-authentication-authorization-roles">14. Authentication, authorization &amp; roles</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>AuthN:</strong> OAuth2 password flow with JWT for the sandbox; pluggable to SSO/LDAP later.</li>
<li><strong>Roles:</strong></li>
<li>Operator - submit forms, view dashboard/alerts.</li>
<li>Engineer/Analyst - all operator rights + view predictions/history/baselines.</li>
<li>Admin - manage config (dropdowns, signals, prediction targets), users; cannot delete (deactivate only).</li>
<li><strong>AuthZ:</strong> role checks on API routes; admin/config endpoints restricted.</li>
<li><strong>Audit:</strong> all config changes and key data edits recorded in <code>audit_log</code>.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="15-observability-logging-monitoring">15. Observability, logging &amp; monitoring</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Structured logging</strong> across all services (ingestion, feature engine, ML, API) with correlation IDs.</li>
<li><strong>Health/metrics:</strong> extend <code>/health</code> to report each service in req. §3 (Backend API, Frontend, ML Service, Data Import, DB, Logging, Auth, Scheduler) + ML models loaded + last successful ingest time + scheduler status.</li>
<li><strong>Pipeline metrics:</strong> ingest lag, rows/min, feature-compute time, prediction latency, model staleness.</li>
<li><strong>Dashboards/alerts on the system itself</strong> (e.g. ingestion stopped, DB disk, model not retrained).</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="16-security-data-governance">16. Security &amp; data governance</h2>
<ul>
<li>Secrets via environment variables / secret store (never in code) - extends ZITTA's <code>os.getenv</code> config approach.</li>
<li>TLS for API and DB connections; least-privilege DB user for the app.</li>
<li>Per-tenant data isolation enforced by <code>company_id</code> scoping.</li>
<li>Backups (see §17) and documented restore procedure.</li>
<li>PII is minimal (operator names) - restrict access by role; retain per policy.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="17-deployment-infrastructure-req-3">17. Deployment &amp; infrastructure - req. §3</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Sandbox server</strong> provisioned by DevOps; ZITTA codebase copied; fresh empty PostgreSQL created.</li>
<li><strong>Containerization:</strong> Docker images per service (api, ingestion, ml, frontend) orchestrated with docker-compose (sandbox) -&gt; Kubernetes optional later.</li>
<li><strong>Services to run &amp; verify</strong> (req. §3): Backend API, Frontend, ML Service, Data Import, Database, Logging, Authentication, Scheduler/Jobs.</li>
<li><strong>Configuration:</strong> all environment-specific values via env vars (DB connection, API source, poll interval, retention windows, thresholds).</li>
<li><strong>Migrations:</strong> Alembic on deploy; seed <code>signal_catalog</code> + <code>config_dropdown</code> from the English seeds.</li>
<li><strong>Backups:</strong> scheduled PostgreSQL dumps (daily) + retention; documented restore. Backup target is an open item (§23).</li>
<li><strong>Environments:</strong> sandbox now; clear path to staging/prod with the same images and separate databases.</li>
<li><strong>Deliverables (req. §10 DevOps):</strong> running sandbox, server overview, deployment documentation.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="18-testing-qa">18. Testing &amp; QA</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Unit tests:</strong> feature calculations, factor scaling, dropdown/config logic, API validation.</li>
<li><strong>Integration tests:</strong> ingestion -&gt; DB -&gt; feature window -&gt; prediction path; form submit -&gt; DB.</li>
<li><strong>Data tests:</strong> signal-catalog import correctness, factor application (e.g. 2300 x 0.1 = 230.0), label-join correctness.</li>
<li><strong>ML tests:</strong> training reproducibility, evaluation-gate enforcement, schema of <code>ml_prediction</code>.</li>
<li><strong>E2E:</strong> operator form flows in the frontend.</li>
<li><strong>CI:</strong> run tests on each change; lint/type-check (TypeScript + Python).</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2 id="19-reuse-vs-build-new-vs-drop-zitta-sunpor">19. Reuse vs build new vs drop (ZITTA -&gt; SUNPOR)</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Reuse</th>
<th>Build new</th>
<th>Drop / abstract</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Poll-&gt;buffer-&gt;features-&gt;state-&gt;score-&gt;store loop (<code>main.py</code>)</td>
<td>Multi-tenant Postgres schema (15 tables)</td>
<td>Hardcoded <code>Val_x</code> mappings (<code>config.py</code>)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Windowing approach (5/30 min)</td>
<td>Catalog-driven ingestion + factor scaling</td>
<td>Fixed regimes <code>REGIME_LOW_MAX</code> etc.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Isolation-Forest anomaly modules</td>
<td>8 operator UI forms + React frontend</td>
<td>Single-machine assumptions</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>FastAPI service pattern</td>
<td>Supervised Models 3-6 (label-driven)</td>
<td>ZITTA-specific baseline CSV pipeline</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Retrain scheduler + drift detector</td>
<td>Label-join training pipeline + MLOps registry</td>
<td>SQLite as primary DB</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>State-classifier approach (Model 1)</td>
<td>Alerting, Auth/roles, config admin UI</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>/health</code> + model registry patterns</td>
<td>Time-series partitioning/retention</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
