<hr />
<h2 id="21-delivery-plan-priority-order-req-11">21. Delivery plan (priority order) - req. §11</h2>
<p><strong>Priority 1 - Foundation:</strong> sandbox + copy ZITTA + fresh PostgreSQL; 15-table schema + migrations; import SignalExport -&gt; <code>signal_catalog</code>; build 8 UI forms with dynamic dropdowns.</p>
<p><strong>Priority 2 - Data capture:</strong> production-run lifecycle; operator events, material behavior, material blocking, daily quality wired end-to-end.</p>
<p><strong>Priority 3 - Core ML:</strong> config-driven feature-engineering layer; Model 1 (Process State) + Model 2 (Low Production).</p>
<p><strong>Priority 4 - Predictive ML:</strong> Models 3-6 trained once enough operator labels are collected.</p>
<p>(Cross-cutting infra - auth, alerting, observability, backups - is layered in alongside Priorities 1-2.)</p>
<hr />
<h2 id="22-acceptance-criteria-req-14">22. Acceptance criteria - req. §14</h2>
<p>At the end of preparation, SUNPOR must:
1. Run on the new sandbox.
2. Have a fresh, SUNPOR-specific database.
3. Import and categorize all SignalExport signals.
4. Implement all UI forms from the input form.
5. Let operators record production events, maintenance, faults, material behavior.
6. Allow retrospective quality data entry.
7. Record material blocks with period + reason.
8. Link production runs to a material type.
9. Distinguish production phases via ML.
10. Recognize Low Production separately.
11. Be structurally prepared (data-wise) for Predictive Quality.
12. Be cleanly SUNPOR-specific, no longer ZITTA-specific.</p>
<hr />
<h2 id="23-open-items-decisions-needed">23. Open items / decisions needed</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Live data source</strong> - actual WinCC/OPC connection details for Line E10 (host, protocol, poll rate). Until then, develop against historical exports.</li>
<li><strong>TimescaleDB vs plain PostgreSQL</strong> for <code>signal_timeseries</code> (depends on what the sandbox can install).</li>
<li><strong>Retention windows</strong> - how long to keep raw vs downsampled history.</li>
<li><strong>Auth provider</strong> - simple JWT now vs SSO/LDAP integration target.</li>
<li><strong>Shift definitions</strong> (names/times) to seed the <code>shift</code> dropdown.</li>
<li><strong>Duplicate process-water temperature</strong> - two tags for "Process Water Temperature Actual" (<code>E10GProzesswasserTemperatur</code> WORD x0.1 and <code>EX10I203_temp</code> REAL x1). Confirm authoritative one.</li>
<li><strong>Alert delivery channels</strong> beyond in-app (email/Teams/webhook?).</li>
<li><strong>Backup target &amp; schedule</strong> for the sandbox.</li>
</ol></body></html>